Patch summary:
Raise the software AVC codec limits enough for high-resolution desktop capture
and playback paths used by the VM. Desktop windows and host displays can exceed
phone/tablet-era software encoder assumptions, especially when capturing large
surfaces or streaming a full desktop-sized framebuffer.

The patch adjusts advertised codec capabilities and matching encoder limits
together, so framework capability checks and actual software codec behavior stay
aligned.

